seriously, that hurts...

227
00:12:34,166 --> 00:12:36,750
Doesn't matter...
What you fail to understand

228
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:38,750
is that all of this
is far from over.

229
00:12:38,833 --> 00:12:40,750
In fact, I'm just
getting started!

230
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:42,916
Be warned, I will
utterly destroy

231
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,375
the Hanshin Police Force.

232
00:12:44,458 --> 00:12:45,833
And that's not all.

233
00:12:45,916 --> 00:12:48,250
I will bring down
all of Osaka with you!

234
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:50,750
I'm sure you'll all going
to be looking forward to it.

235
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:53,083
We gotta stop him.

236
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:55,500
Chief Katsu, is this a
claim of responsibility?

237
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,541
Did the caller identify himself?

238
00:12:57,625 --> 00:12:59,500
Please, everyone calm down!

239
00:12:59,583 --> 00:13:00,958
Later today,

240
00:13:01,041 --> 00:13:02,458
Chief Katsu will meet with
top officials from R.A.P.T.

241
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:04,750
to discuss strategies for
combating the terrorist threat.

242
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:07,625
From The National Diet
Building, I'm Sean Billings.

243
00:13:07,708 --> 00:13:10,916
This can't... be real?
Can it, Inspector?

244
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,125
Wish I could tell ya.

245
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:14,625
Hey, I got a lead to
check out, all right?

246
00:13:21,166 --> 00:13:23,208
Time to do a
little detective work?

247
00:13:23,291 --> 00:13:25,291
You recognize that logo?

248
00:13:25,375 --> 00:13:28,166
It was on that train we were
chasing a few weeks back.

249
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:29,750
Yeah, so?

250
00:13:29,833 --> 00:13:31,833
This might have something to do
with that creature you ran into.

251
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:34,375
You did say it had
the same glowing brain.

252
00:13:34,458 --> 00:13:38,375
But why did the truck come
here to this abandoned park.

253
00:13:38,458 --> 00:13:40,958
That's what we're
about to find out.

254
00:13:43,958 --> 00:13:44,583
What is it?

255
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:46,375
The driver's been shot!

256
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:47,666
What? It's a set up?

257
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:48,666
A trap...

258
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:50,000
Get down!

259
00:13:51,625 --> 00:13:54,333
Take it easy. You don't have
to be so rough about it.

260
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:56,458
Sorry, didn't mean to be...

261
00:13:56,541 --> 00:13:59,500
Stay under the truck
and keep your head down.

262
00:13:59,583 --> 00:14:00,833
No problem.

263
00:14:09,958 --> 00:14:11,083
There he is!

264
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:18,708
Hey Sei, you can come out now.

265
00:14:38,583 --> 00:14:39,791
Sei!

266
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:51,916
Hey check it out. I'm picking
up a huge EM signal!

267
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,541
And despite its crazy-big size,
my readings say it's flying.

268
00:14:55,625 --> 00:14:56,916
Where's it headed?

269
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,375
Let's see...

270
00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:00,916
Tracking toward something
that looks like Tokyo Tower.

271
00:15:18,916 --> 00:15:21,375
What is that thing?
It's gone berserk!

272
00:15:21,458 --> 00:15:23,000
It's some kind of robot!

273
00:15:23,083 --> 00:15:25,625
You think it can see us in here?

274
00:15:29,083 --> 00:15:32,333
What is that thing
tryin' to do?!

275
00:15:32,416 --> 00:15:35,833
You are witnessing the debut
of the cybot Giganits.

276
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:37,500
Cool, isn't it?

277
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:40,375
Let's cut the small talk.
What are you trying to do?

278
00:15:40,458 --> 00:15:44,833
You're a smart guy.
Why don't you figure it out?

279
00:15:44,916 --> 00:15:46,208
How original.

280
00:15:46,291 --> 00:15:48,250
You're gonna blow up
Tsutenkaku Tower, aren't you?

281
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:49,708
You know, I hadn't
thought of that,

282
00:15:49,791 --> 00:15:52,208
but it's an interesting idea.

283
00:15:52,291 --> 00:15:55,875
You wouldn't dare...!
I will hunt you down!

284
00:15:55,958 --> 00:15:58,958
Ooh, scary!
The detective who's too busy

285
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:02,791
for his own family has
a really nasty temper.

286
00:16:02,875 --> 00:16:06,916
What? What did you say?

287
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,166
Attention, we have an
emergency situation.

288
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:11,333
All mobile and attack
units report to the tower

289
00:16:11,416 --> 00:16:14,125
and establish a defensive
perimeter immediately!

290
00:16:14,208 --> 00:16:16,750
A rogue cybot is attempting
to destroy the tower!

291
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,041
Roger!

292
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:20,958
You sons of bitches...!

293
00:16:21,041 --> 00:16:23,583
I'll turn y'all into
sashimi, you hear me?!

294
00:16:23,666 --> 00:16:27,041
Yeah! Get the hell
out of our town!

295
00:16:27,125 --> 00:16:29,125
Dang! That thing's huge...

296
00:16:29,208 --> 00:16:30,958
Well, go get him!

297
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,250
I love the way an
historic structure can

298
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:38,958
captivate the public and come
to symbolize an entire city...

299
00:16:39,041 --> 00:16:42,416
Tsutenkaku Tower
is one of those.

300
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:46,416
Why are you making me
sit here and watch this?

301
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:49,458
No real reason, my good Chief...

302
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:51,958
I just wanted you to
have a front row seat

303
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:55,000
for the collapse of Osaka.

304
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:56,250
When this is over,

305
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:58,625
a great opportunity will
have presented itself.

306
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:00,041
And, what's that...?

307
00:17:00,125 --> 00:17:02,333
Are you gonna take over Osaka?

308
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:04,041
To be perfectly frank...

309
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:07,708
I've always been a little bit
jealous of you out there.

310
00:17:07,791 --> 00:17:09,375
How's that?

311
00:17:12,583 --> 00:17:15,291
Osaka's great sense
of community...

312
00:17:15,375 --> 00:17:17,791
How can Tokyo even
hope to compare?

313
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:20,166
Our streets are littered
with worthless vermin

314
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:21,666
and unchecked immigrants.

315
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:24,916
You see, that's the
reason I created RAPT.

316
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,833
To eliminate those
unwanted elements

317
00:17:26,916 --> 00:17:29,000
and rebuild a solid community.

318
00:17:29,083 --> 00:17:32,416
Interesting... Y'know
you're quite insane.

319
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,625
If you go along with us,
we can avoid

320
00:17:34,708 --> 00:17:38,250
the real unpleasantness that
most certainly will follow.

321
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:41,166
I'm sure we can work out
a suitable "bargain."

322
00:17:41,250 --> 00:17:44,916
We must defend the tower!
We must defend Osaka!

323
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:49,375
Honor our history...!
Remember Osaka Castle!

324
00:17:49,458 --> 00:17:50,625
Don't get upset.

325
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:52,958
Who the hell do
you think you are?

326
00:17:53,041 --> 00:17:56,916
You and your corruption made
Tokyo into the cesspool it is!

327
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,875
The will of the
people still thrives

328
00:17:58,958 --> 00:18:02,625
on our side of the Hakone Wall!

329
00:18:02,708 --> 00:18:06,583
If you want Osaka...
then fight us!

330
00:18:07,958 --> 00:18:12,375
I'm sure you'll fight bravely,
but you just can't win.

331
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:16,375
This is Inspector
Masa of Tiger-1!

332
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:19,458
All units open fire!
Aim for the torso!

333
00:18:22,791 --> 00:18:24,000
Yeah, kill it!

334
00:18:24,083 --> 00:18:26,375
Die you gravy sucking pig!

335
00:18:29,083 --> 00:18:30,833
Hell, yeah!

336
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,125
Takane...

337
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:04,500
Inspector Iriki...! Inspector,
where are you...? Inspe--

338
00:19:05,666 --> 00:19:07,000
Masa-yan.

339
00:19:07,083 --> 00:19:10,708
Hey... I can't--I can't
find Inspector Iriki.

340
00:19:10,791 --> 00:19:14,541
Is he with you...? Masa-yan?

341
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:18,250
Takane... will you
do me a favor?

342
00:19:21,041 --> 00:19:23,375
My daughter turned
three today...

343
00:19:23,458 --> 00:19:26,958
When she's old enough,
tell her about me.

344
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:30,125
Tell her about what
kind of cop I was.

345
00:19:30,208 --> 00:19:31,666
It would mean a lot...

346
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:36,500
Oh, yeah... Don't take any
shit from those traitors!

347
00:19:36,583 --> 00:19:40,625
Osaka's justice will never die!

348
00:19:40,708 --> 00:19:42,375
Masa-yan!

349
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:49,375
Milly...! I was...
a good cop...!

350
00:19:49,458 --> 00:19:52,416
I lived to serve
the city I loved...!

351
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:57,708
Your father died so
that you could live!

352
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:06,666
How ya like that...?!

353
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:08,833
Here! Y'want another taste?!

354
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:39,208
What the--?

355
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:43,750
Hurry!

356
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,541
I know, I know!

357
00:20:45,625 --> 00:20:47,458
Who the hell are you guys?

358
00:20:47,541 --> 00:20:50,583
You're Takane of the Elite
Division, Hawk Squad, right?

359
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:51,750
Yeah...

360
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,583
That's Jo taking care
of things for you.

361
00:21:06,166 --> 00:21:07,291
Not good...

362
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:23,875
You let go of Jo...!
Let go! Let go!

363
00:21:26,208 --> 00:21:29,833
Gigantis, go ahead and crush
that thing like a tin can.

364
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:38,625
C'mon! We need to get
to the trailer now!

365
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:50,708
Why...? You traitor...

366
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,500
You traitor!

367
00:22:15,666 --> 00:22:19,458
I don't know why I can't move

368
00:22:19,541 --> 00:22:23,333
My mind is lost in this cloud

369
00:22:23,416 --> 00:22:30,708
No one even hears my voice
and my tears fall to the ground

370
00:22:30,791 --> 00:22:38,333
It's like my feelings of
loneliness are falling too

371
00:22:38,416 --> 00:22:43,625
The truth is that we
all just want to smile

372
00:22:43,708 --> 00:22:47,875
and smile with each other

373
00:22:47,958 --> 00:22:51,083
It hurts inside
when we don't...

374
00:22:51,166 --> 00:22:54,708
we don't... we don't
know what to say

375
00:22:54,791 --> 00:22:59,458
I only hope that
someone will be there,

376
00:22:59,541 --> 00:23:03,541
and be watching over me

377
00:23:03,625 --> 00:23:05,541
so take my hand,

378
00:23:05,625 --> 00:23:14,333
we'll walk tonight
underneath the sky

379
00:23:31,833 --> 00:23:36,833
Justice spoiled; trust
betrayed; sadness endured...

380
00:23:36,916 --> 00:23:38,666
And unlikely heroes

381
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:41,791
who rise from the brink of
despair and destruction...

382
00:23:41,875 --> 00:23:45,666
Next Burst Angel:
"Showdown in Osaka."

